just_use essays.go

# label: SPIKE (essays-landing)
# role: supports feature — first-class essay landing in the Gopher portal

V1 (2026-04-17). Lists every `*.md` in `showell/claude_writings/`
(except `QUEUE.md`, `README.md`), sorted newest-first by file
mtime. Each row shows the essay's title (from its first `# `
heading) and mtime in US Eastern (`America/New_York`), formatted
`Jan 2, 2006 · 3:04 PM MST`.

Linked from the Claude card on the Gopher landing page.
Individual essays open via the existing docs route, which renders
the markdown + injects the article-comments script.

Future refinements to expect:
- Date source: currently file mtime, which rebases when files
  are edited. Swap to git first-commit timestamp if Steve wants
  stable "written on" dates.
- Body previews / excerpts.
- Tag or category filters (status reports vs reflective essays
  vs plan essays).
